<h2 id="step-function">Step function</h2>
<p>Function composed of several functions boxcar $f_{\rm BC}(x)$ is a step function $f_{\rm S}(x)$. Or we can say that a step function $f_{\rm S}(x)$ is a finite linear combination of boxcar functions $f_{\rm BC}(x)$ of intervals, which is simply</p>

<p>\begin{equation}
\label{eqn:vsf-step-function}
{\rm step}(x) = \sum_{i = 1}^N f_{ {\rm BC}, i}(x),
\end{equation}</p>

<p>where each $f_{ {\rm BC}, i}(x)$ has its own values of $A_i$, $a_i$, and $b_i$.</p>

<oo>
