<h2 id="exercises">Exercises</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Suppose that there are two boxcar function with $A_1 = 2$, $a_1 = 1$, $b_1 = 2$ and $A_2 = -2$, $a_2 = 2$, $b_2 = 3$, draw the functions, each in a separated graph.</li>
  <li>Wite the equation of each boxchar funtion $f_{ {\rm BC}, 1}$, $f_{ {\rm BC}, 2}$, and $f_{ {\rm BC}, 3}$ in Fig. <a href="#fig:fig:vsf-boxchar-example">2</a>.</li>
  <li>What are the values of $f(7)$,  $f(1)$, and  $f(4)$ from the step function in Fig. <a href="#fig:vsf-step">3</a>?</li>
  <li>Please write the equation of step function velocity $v(t)$ from graph shown in Fig. <a href="#fig:vsf-step-5-intv">4</a>.</li>
  <li>Could you also calculate the total displacement of object $\Delta x$ from $t = 0$ to $t = 8 \ \rm s$, whose velocity function is given in Fig. <a href="#fig:vsf-step-5-intv">4</a>? Calculate it if you are able to do that.</li>
</ol>

